# Municipal Data (2022) and Digital Elevation Model

## **Project Overview**  
This repository contains data and R scripts for analyzing municipal data from 2022, including population statistics, land and water area, terrain steepness, and roughness. The dataset provides valuable insights for urban planning, agriculture, and environmental assessment.

## **Data Sources**  
The datasets used in this project are sourced from:  
- **ISTAT**: [Statistica Sperimentale - Indici Morfometrici](https://www.istat.it/statistica-sperimentale/indici-per-la-descrizione-morfometrica-del-territorio-italiano/)  
- **Open Data Soft**: [Georeferenced Italy Municipality Shapefile](https://public.opendatasoft.com/explore/dataset/georef-italy-comune/export/)  

Ensure that the data files are placed in the correct directory before running the scripts.


## **How to Use the Code**
This repository contains R scripts for data processing, merging, and visualization.  

### **1. Uploading Morphometric Data**
Ensure you have the required libraries installed:  
```r
library(readxl)
library(tidyverse)
df <- read_excel("Indici-morfometrici.xlsx")
colnames(df) <- df[1, ] 
df <- df[-1, ]  
head(df)
